<div class="content bottom">
    <h2>Sigiriya</h2>
    <p class="m-4">Sigiriya is an ancient rock fortress, which belonged to many kings in Sri Lanka. In other words, this was a fully secured palace. Eventually some people call this the “Lion Rock”. It is because of the lion-feet structure at the bottom entrance of the rock. UNESCO named Sigiriya as a World Heritage Site. Historical facts are proving that the ancient king Ravana was the builder of Sigiriya. This site is world famous because of its amazing architecture and fresco paintings.

        Furthermore, Sigiriya is one of the best places to visit in Sri Lanka for a history explorer. Water garden of Sigiriya is the other amazing part. It is a garden with lots of ponds and fountains. On the other hand, the mirror wall is actually mirroring the ancient Sri Lankan literature.</p>
    <img src="static/img/sigiriya.jpg" alt="" class="center-img">
    <h2 class="m-top-3">Polonnaruwa</h2>
    <p class="m-4">Polonnaruwa is one of the best places to visit in Sri Lanka. Consequently losing the first kingdom Anuradhapura, Sinhalese kings formed a new kingdom. It was Polonnaruwa where a visitor can explore number of ancient ruins. In fact that you may find two types of ruins which are belonging to two cultures. If you ever visit Polonnaruwa make sure not to miss exploring of the historic irrigation around the city.

        UNESCO named this ancient city as a world heritage site. The city fills with ancient stone carvings, statues, brick works, stone works, paintings and many other artistic structures. This is the only ancient city in Sri Lanka, a visitor can view large number of ruins in a small area.</p>
    <img src="static/img/polonnaruwa.jpg" alt="" class="center-img">
